The Funda Zophila Foundation along with Bayview SAPS and the Community Policing Forum (CPF) recently launched their Gender- Based Violence programme for 2019.The group held a placard demonstration, along Higginson Highway, on prevention of bullying and abuse in the community. Bayview SAPS spokesperson, Colin Chetty, said: “The volunteers have sent a strong message to the community, that together we stand against any form of bullying and abuse, by means of slogans on the placards.”